<br>
General Chat Rules<br>
- Always be polite and show respect <br>
- Remember you represent the guild <br>
- A guild officer can use discretion to tighten or loosen these rules during a guild event, raid, or grouping. <br>
<br>
Guild Chat<br>
These rules are flexible. Bottom line is, don't overuse guild chat.<br>
<br>
Guild chat should be used for:<br>
- Guild Events <br>
- Asking Questions - Answer should be done in a /tell <br>
- Organizing groups <br>
- Selling items <br>
- Ding momentous occasions <br>
- Hello and goodnight is still accepted <br>
- Small conversations in role play (an officer can request that a conversation be taken to /tell or group) <br>
- Real life discussions should be kept out of guild chat.<br>
- Not giving a play by play of your EQ life<br>
<br>
Shouts<br>
Please remember that when you shout, everyone in the zone sees it (unless they have shout turned off).  Even if you go anonymous, it is still possible to do a /guildstatus on someone to find out their guild status.  This also applies to OOC  <br>
- Using shout when looking for a group is acceptable. <br>
- Shout should always be done in Role Play. <br>
- Shout when there is a train coming through<br>
- We should not use Shout for raids, events, auctioning, or putting anyone down (exceptions are made when chat channels are down)<br>
<br>
OOC<br>
- Using OOC when looking for a group is acceptable<br>
- Answering a question in OOC when asked in OOC is acceptable. Using /tell is also good.<br>
- When you feel the need to speak Out of Character<br>
- OOC is not an opportunity to slander, put down, or in anyway make offense comments to or about specific players.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Guild Chat Channels</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
The guild officers have setup a few chat channels for official guild use. Of course you are welcome to use your own in other cases.<br>
 <br>
First, tips on use:<br>
Create a hotbutton to join the channels, if many, when you log in. <br>
<br>
/join bbscofoj<br>
This is our alliance chat channel with the Fists of Justice.<br>
<br>
/join bbsco:raid<br>
This is our primary raid chat line. The raid/event lead will let you know when to use this line.<br>
 <br>
/join bbsco2:raid<br>
We sometimes have more than one raid per night, so this is our secondary raid chat line. The raid/event lead will let you know when to use this line.<br>
 <br>
/join bbsco3:raid<br>
You get the picture.  <br>
 <br>
Officers have their own chat channel as well, but that is discussed on the officer site.<br>
 <br>
If you have any questions, please speak with a guild officer.<br>
